obj_root_law_sections_1:
  sectionId (2203)
  sectionNo (1)
  orderNo 1
  title `Short title, extent and commencement.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_1_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_1_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_11_12_00004_196322_1517807320141&sectionId=2203&sectionno=1&orderno=1&orgactid=AC_CEN_11_12_00004_196322_1517807320141
obj_root_law_sections_1_content:
  string
  line `(1) This Act may be called the Export (Quality Control`
  line `and Inspection) Act, 1963.`
  line
  line `(2) It extends to the whole of India.`
  line
  line `(3) It shall come into force on such date ^1`
  line `as the Central Government may, by Notification in the`
  line `Official Gazette, appoint.`
obj_root_law_sections_1_footnotes:
  string
  line `1 1st January, 1964, vide notification No. S.O. 3604(E), dated the 30th December, 1963, see Gazette of India, Extraordinary, Part`
  line `II, Sec. 3(ii).`
obj_root_law_sections_2:
  sectionId (2204)
  sectionNo (2)
  orderNo 2
  title Definitions.
  content obj_root_law_sections_2_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_2_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_11_12_00004_196322_1517807320141&sectionId=2204&sectionno=2&orderno=2&orgactid=AC_CEN_11_12_00004_196322_1517807320141
obj_root_law_sections_2_content:
  string
  line `In this Act, unless the context otherwise requires,--`
  line
  line ^1
  line `[(a) "adjudicating authority" means the authority specified in, or under, section 10K;`
  line
  line `(ab) "Appellate authority" means the appellate authority referred to in section 10M;]`
  line
  line ^2
  line `[(ac)]"Council" means the Export Inspection Council established under section 3;`
  line
  line `(b) "export", with its grammatical variations and cognate expressions, means taking out of India`
  line `to a place outside India;`
  line
  line `(c) "inspection", in relation to a commodity, means the process of determining whether a batch of`
  line `goods in that commodity complies with the standard specifications applicable to it or any other`
  line `specifications stipulated in the export contract generally by inspecting either the whole batch or a`
  line `selected sample or samples which purport to represent the whole batch;`
  line
  line `(d) "notified commodity" means any commodity notified under clause (a) of section 6;`
  line
  line `(e) "prescribed" means prescribed by rules made under this Act;`
  line
  line `(f) "quality control" means any activity having for its object the determination of the quality of a`
  line `commodity (whether during the process of manufacture or production or subsequently) in order to`
  line `ascertain whether it satisfies the standard specifications applicable to it or any other specifications`
  line `stipulated in the export contract and whether it may be accepted for purposes of export.`
obj_root_law_sections_2_footnotes:
  string
  line `1 Ins. by Act 40 of 1984, s. 2 (w.e.f. 2-7-1984).`
  line
  line `2 Clause (a) re-lettered as clause (ac) by s. 2, ibid. (w.e.f. 2-7-1984).`
obj_root_law_sections_3:
  sectionId (2205)
  sectionNo (3)
  orderNo 3
  title `Establishment of Export Inspection Council.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_3_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by s. 3, ibid., for "eleven" (w.e.f. 2-7-1984).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_11_12_00004_196322_1517807320141&sectionId=2205&sectionno=3&orderno=3&orgactid=AC_CEN_11_12_00004_196322_1517807320141
obj_root_law_sections_3_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Central Government may by notification`
  line `in the Official Gazette, establish, with effect from such date as may be specified in the notification, a`
  line `Council to be known as the Export Inspection Council, which shall consist of--`
  line
  line `(a) a Chairman to be appointed by the Central Government;`
  line
  line `(b) the Director of Inspection and Quality Control, ex officio, who shall be the Secretary;`
  line
  line `(c) the Honorary Adviser on Standardization to the Government of India and Director of Indian`
  line `Standards Institution, ex officio;`
  line
  line `(d) the Agricultural Marketing Advisor to the Government of India, ex officio;`
  line
  line `(e) the Director General of Commercial Intelligence and Statistics, ex officio;`
  line
  line `(f)`
  line `^4[fifteen] other members nominated by the Central Government three of whom shall be`
  line `persons representing the agencies referred to in section 7.`
  line
  line `(2) The Council shall be a body corporate by the name aforesaid, having perpetual succession and a`
  line `common seal, with power to acquire, hold and dispose of property and to contract, and shall by the said`
  line `name sue and be sued.`
  line
  line `(3) The term of office of, and the manner of filling casual vacancies among, the members of the`
  line `Council referred to in clauses (a) and (f) of sub-section (1) and the travelling and daily allowances`
  line `payable to the members of the Council and the procedure to be followed in the discharge of its functions`
  line `by the Council shall be such as may be prescribed.`
  line
  line `(4) No act or proceeding of the Council shall be invalidated merely by reason of any vacancy in, or`
  line `any defect in the Constitution of, the Council.`
  line
  line `(5) Subject to such rules as may be made by the Central Government in this behalf, the Council may`
  line `appoint such officers and other employees as it considers necessary for the purpose of discharging its`
  line `functions under this Act.`
obj_root_law_sections_4:
  sectionId (2206)
  sectionNo (4)
  orderNo 4
  title `Director of Inspection and Quality Control.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_4_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_4_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_11_12_00004_196322_1517807320141&sectionId=2206&sectionno=4&orderno=4&orgactid=AC_CEN_11_12_00004_196322_1517807320141
obj_root_law_sections_4_content:
  string
  line `The Central Government shall appoint a Director`
  line `of Inspection and Quality Control to exercise such powers and perform such duties under this Act as may`
  line `be prescribed.`
obj_root_law_sections_4_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_5:
  sectionId (2207)
  sectionNo (5)
  orderNo 5
  title `Functions of the Council.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_5_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_5_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_11_12_00004_196322_1517807320141&sectionId=2207&sectionno=5&orderno=5&orgactid=AC_CEN_11_12_00004_196322_1517807320141
obj_root_law_sections_5_content:
  string
  line `(1) The functions of the Council shall generally be to advise the`
  line `Central Government regarding measures for the enforcement of quality control and inspection in relation`
  line `to commodities intended for export and to draw up programmes therefore, to make, with the concurrence`
  line `of the Central Government, grants-in-aid to the agencies established or recognised under section 7 and to`
  line `perform such other functions as maybe assigned to it by or under this Act.`
  line
  line `(2) For the purpose of performing its functions, the Council may co-opt as members such number of`
  line `persons as it thinks fit who have special knowledge and practical experience in matters relating to any`
  line `commodity or trade therein and any such person shall have the right to take part in the discussions of the`
  line `Council but shall not have the right to vote and shall not be a member for any other purpose.`
  line
  line `(3) The Council may also constitute specialist committees for conducting investigations on special`
  line `problems connected with its functions.`
  line
  line `(4) In the performance of its functions under this Act, the Council shall be bound by such directions`
  line `as the Central Government may give to it in writing from time to time.`
obj_root_law_sections_5_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_6:
  sectionId (2208)
  sectionNo (6)
  orderNo 6
  title `Powers of the Central Government in regard to quality control and inspection.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_6_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_6_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_11_12_00004_196322_1517807320141&sectionId=2208&sectionno=6&orderno=6&orgactid=AC_CEN_11_12_00004_196322_1517807320141
obj_root_law_sections_6_content:
  string
  line `If the Central`
  line `Government, after consulting the Council, is of opinion that it is necessary or expedient so to do for the`
  line `development of the export trade of India, it may, by order published in the Official Gazette,--`
  line
  line `(a) notify commodities which shall be subject to quality control or inspection or both prior to`
  line export;
  line
  line `(b) specify the type of quality control or inspection which will be applied to a notified`
  line commodity;
  line
  line `(c) establish, adopt or recognise one or more standard specifications for a notified commodity;`
  line
  line `(d) prohibit the export in the course of international trade of a notified commodity unless it is`
  line `accompanied by a certificate issued under section 7 that the commodity satisfies the conditions`
  line `relating to quality control or inspection, or it has affixed or applied to it a mark or seal recognised by`
  line `the Central Government as indicating that it conforms to the standard specifications applicable to it`
  line `under clause (c).`
obj_root_law_sections_6_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_7:
  sectionId (2209)
  sectionNo (7)
  orderNo 7
  title `Machinery for quality control and inspection.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_7_content
  footnotes `1. Ins. by Act 40 of 1984, s. 4 (w.e.f. 2-7-1984).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_11_12_00004_196322_1517807320141&sectionId=2209&sectionno=7&orderno=7&orgactid=AC_CEN_11_12_00004_196322_1517807320141
obj_root_law_sections_7_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Central Government may, by`
  line `notification in the Official Gazette, establish, or recognise subject to such conditions as it may deem fit,`
  line `agencies for quality control or inspection or both:`
  line
  line `Provided that if the Central Government is of opinion that any recognition granted to any agency`
  line `under this sub-section should, in the public interest, be withdrawn, the Central Government may after`
  line `giving a reasonable opportunity to that agency to make representations in the matter, withdraw, by like`
  line `notification, the recognition granted to it.`
  line
  line `(2) Any agency referred to in sub-section (1) may, on application made to it or otherwise, hold or`
  line `cause to be held such examination as it thinks fit relating to quality control or inspection of notified`
  line `commodities, either at the time of export or earlier, in such testing houses or by such surveyors or`
  line `samplers as are approved by the Central Government in this behalf and may charge such fees as may be`
  line `prescribed for the purpose of such examination.`
  line
  line `(3) If, after the examination, the agency is of opinion that the commodity satisfies the standard`
  line `specifications laid down in respect of it under section 6 or, as the case may be, any other specifications`
  line `stipulated in the export contract, it may issue a certificate that the commodity satisfies the conditions`
  line `relating to quality control and inspection.`
  line
  line `^1[(3A) Where the agency has reason to believe that a certificate issued under sub-section (3) has been`
  line `obtained fraudulently or by misrepresentation, or the commodity in relation to, which the certificate is`
  line `issued has been changed or has deteriorated in quality, the agency may, by order, amend, suspend or`
  line `cancel the certificate in such manner and subject to such procedure as may be prescribed:`
  line
  line `Provided that before amending, a suspending or cancelling any such certificate the holder thereof`
  line `shall be given a reasonable opportunity of being heard.]`
  line
  line `(4) Any person aggrieved by the refusal of any agency referred to in sub-section (1) to issue a`
  line `certificate, ^1[or by the amendment, suspension or cancellation of a certificate under sub-section (3A)] may`
  line `prefer an appeal within such time as may be prescribed to such authority as the Central Government may,`
  line `by notification in the Official Gazette, constitute for the purpose of hearing appeals.`
  line
  line `(5) Subject to the provisions of sub-section (6), the decision of the agency where no appeal is filed,`
  line `and the decision of the appellate authority where an appeal is filed, shall be final and shall not be`
  line `questioned in any Court of law.`
  line
  line `(6) The Central Government may, at any time, call for and examine the record of any proceeding`
  line `relating to any decision of an agency or appellate authority under this section for the purpose of satisfying`
  line `itself as to the legality or propriety of such decision and may pass such order thereon as it thinks fit.`
obj_root_law_sections_8:
  sectionId (2210)
  sectionNo (8)
  orderNo 8
  title `Power to recognise or establish marks to denote conformity with standard specifications.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_8_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_8_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_11_12_00004_196322_1517807320141&sectionId=2210&sectionno=8&orderno=8&orgactid=AC_CEN_11_12_00004_196322_1517807320141
obj_root_law_sections_8_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Central Government may, by notification in the Official Gazette, recognise or establish any mark`
  line `or seal in relation to a notified commodity for the purpose of denoting that such commodity conforms to a`
  line `standard specification applicable to it.`
  line
  line `(2) Any such mark or seal affixed or applied to a notified commodity or to any covering containing,`
  line `or label attached to, such commodity shall be deemed to be evidence of the commodity being in`
  line `conformity with the standard specifications applicable to it under this Act:`
  line
  line `Provided that nothing in this sub-section shall prevent any officer of customs from examining any`
  line `consignment of a notified commodity intended for export if he has reason to believe that the seal or mark`
  line `is not genuine or has been affixed or applied fraudulently or if such an examination is necessary for the`
  line `purpose of any other law for the time being in force.`
obj_root_law_sections_8_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_9:
  sectionId (2211)
  sectionNo (9)
  orderNo 9
  title `Power to obtain information from exporters, etc.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_9_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_9_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_11_12_00004_196322_1517807320141&sectionId=2211&sectionno=9&orderno=9&orgactid=AC_CEN_11_12_00004_196322_1517807320141
obj_root_law_sections_9_content:
  string
  line `The Central Government or any officer or`
  line `authority authorised by it in this behalf may, by notice published in the Official Gazette, require--`
  line
  line `(i) persons manufacturing, dealing in or exporting notified commodities; and`
  line
  line `(ii) such other persons as may be prescribed;`
  line
  line `to furnish any information, return or report which the Central Government or such officer or authority`
  line `may consider necessary for carrying out the purposes of this Act.`
obj_root_law_sections_9_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_10:
  sectionId (2212)
  sectionNo (10)
  orderNo 10
  title `Finance, accounts and audit.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_10_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_10_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_11_12_00004_196322_1517807320141&sectionId=2212&sectionno=10&orderno=10&orgactid=AC_CEN_11_12_00004_196322_1517807320141
obj_root_law_sections_10_content:
  string
  line `(1) For the purpose of enabling the Council to discharge its`
  line `functions under this Act, the Central Government may, after due appropriation made by Parliament by`
  line `law in this behalf, pay to the Council such sums of money as that Government considers necessary by`
  line `way of grants, loans or otherwise.`
  line
  line `(2) For the purpose of discharging its functions under this Act, the Council may receive grants or`
  line `donations from bodies and institutions approved by the Central Government in this behalf.`
  line
  line `(3) The Council shall have its own fund to which shall be credited the sums of money referred to in`
  line `sub-sections (1) and (2) and the moneys in the fund shall be applied for--`
  line
  line `(a) meeting the pay and allowances of the officers and other employees of the Council and other`
  line `administrative expenses of the Council;`
  line
  line `(b) carrying out the functions of the Council under this Act.`
  line
  line `(4) The Council shall prepare, before the commencement of each financial year, a statement of`
  line `programme of its activities during that year as well as a financial estimate in respect thereof.`
  line
  line `(5) A statement prepared under sub-section (4) shall, not later than three months before the`
  line `commencement of each financial year, be submitted for approval to the Central Government.`
  line
  line `(6) The Council shall maintain such accounts and prepare the balance-sheet in such form as may, in`
  line `consultation with the Comptroller and Auditor-General of India, be prescribed.`
  line
  line `(7) The accounts of the Council shall be audited in such manner and at such times as may, in`
  line `consultation with the Comptroller and Auditor-General of India, be prescribed.`
obj_root_law_sections_10_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_10_a:
  sectionId (2213)
  sectionNo 10A
  orderNo 11
  title `Power to enter and inspect.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_10_a_content
  footnotes `1. Ins. by Act 40 of 1984, s. 5 (w.e.f. 2-7-1984).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_11_12_00004_196322_1517807320141&sectionId=2213&sectionno=10A&orderno=11&orgactid=AC_CEN_11_12_00004_196322_1517807320141
obj_root_law_sections_10_a_content:
  string
  line `^1[10A. Power to enter and inspect.--The Director of Inspection and Quality Control or any officer`
  line `of the Central Government authorised by him in writing in this behalf (hereinafter referred to as the`
  line `"authorised officer") may enter at any reasonable time, any premises which--`
  line
  line `(a) any commodity which has been changed after inspection by any agency referred to in`
  line `sub-section (1) of section 7; or`
  line
  line `(b) any books of account or other documents or things which, in his opinion, will be useful for, or`
  line `relevant to, any proceeding under this Act,`
  line
  line `are suspected to have been kept or concealed, and inspect such commodity, books of account, other`
  line `documents or things and may take such notes or extracts from such books of account or, other documents`
  line `as he may think fit.]`
obj_root_law_sections_10_b:
  sectionId (2214)
  sectionNo 10B
  orderNo 12
  title `Power to search.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_10_b_content
  footnotes `1. Ins. by Act 40 of 1984, s. 5 (w.e.f. 2-7-1984).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_11_12_00004_196322_1517807320141&sectionId=2214&sectionno=10B&orderno=12&orgactid=AC_CEN_11_12_00004_196322_1517807320141
obj_root_law_sections_10_b_content:
  string
  line `^1[10B. Power to search.--If the authorised officer has any reason to believe that--`
  line
  line `(a) any commodity which has been changed after inspection by any agency referred to`
  line `sub-section (1) of section 7; or`
  line
  line `(b) any books of account or other documents or things which, in his opinion, will be useful for, or`
  line `relevant to, any proceeding under this Act,`
  line
  line `are secreted in any place, he may enter into and search such place or premises for such commodity, books`
  line `of account, other documents or things.]`
obj_root_law_sections_10_c:
  sectionId (2215)
  sectionNo 10C
  orderNo 13
  title `Power to seize commodities, etc.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_10_c_content
  footnotes `1. Ins. by Act 40 of 1984, s. 5 (w.e.f. 2-7-1984).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_11_12_00004_196322_1517807320141&sectionId=2215&sectionno=10C&orderno=13&orgactid=AC_CEN_11_12_00004_196322_1517807320141
obj_root_law_sections_10_c_content:
  string
  line `^1[10C. Power to seize commodities, etc.--(1) If the authorised officer has any reason to believe that`
  line `any commodity is liable to confiscation under this Act, he may seize such commodity together with the`
  line `package, covering or receptacle, if any, in which such commodity is found and where such commodity is`
  line `found to have been mixed with any other goods or materials, he may seize such commodity together with`
  line `the goods or materials with which it is so mixed:`
  line
  line `Provided that where it is not practicable to seize any such commodity, the authorised officer may`
  line `serve on the owner of the commodity an order that he shall not remove, part with, or otherwise deal with,`
  line `the commodity except with the previous permission of such authorised officer.`
  line
  line `(2) Where any commodity is seized under sub-section (1) and no notice in respect thereof is given`
  line `under section 10L within six months of the seizure of such commodity, it shall be returned to the person`
  line `from whose possession it was seized:`
  line
  line `Provided that the aforesaid period of six months may, on sufficient cause being shown, be extended`
  line `by the Director of Inspection and Quality Control by a further period not exceeding six months.`
  line
  line `(3) The authorised officer may seize any documents or things which, in his opinion will be useful for,`
  line `or relevant to, any proceeding under this Act.`
  line
  line `(4) The person from whose custody any documents are seized under sub-section (3) shall be entitled`
  line `to make copies thereof or take extracts there from in the presence of the authorised officer.`
  line
  line `(5) If any person legally entitled to the documents or things seized under sub-section (3)objects, for`
  line `any reason, to the retention by the authorised officer of the documents or things, he may make an`
  line `application to the Central Government staling therein the reasons for such objection and requesting for the`
  line `return of the documents or things.`
  line
  line `(6) On receipt of an application under sub-section (5), the Central Government may, after giving the`
  line `applicant an opportunity of being heard, pass such order as it may think fit.`
  line
  line `(7) Where any document--`
  line
  line `(a) is produced or furnished by any person or has been seized from the custody or control of any`
  line `person under this Act or any other law for the time being in force; or`
  line
  line `(b) has been received from any place outside India (duly authenticated by such authority or`
  line `person and in such manner as may be prescribed) in the course of the investigation of any offence`
  line `alleged to have been committed by any person against this Act,`
  line
  line `and such document is tendered in evidence against the person by whom it is produced or from whom it`
  line `was seized or against such person and any other person who is jointly tried, or proceeded against, with`
  line `him, the Court, or, as the case may be, the adjudicating authority shall, notwithstanding anything to the`
  line `contrary contained in any other law for the time being in force,--`
  line
  line `(i) presume, unless the contrary is proved, that the signature and every other part of such`
  line `document which purports to be in the handwriting of any particular person or which the court or`
  line `the adjudicating authority may reasonably assume to have been signed by, or to be in the`
  line `handwriting of, any particular person, is under that person's handwriting, and, in the case of a`
  line `document executed or attested, it was executed or attested by the person by whom it purports to`
  line `have been so executed or attested;`
  line
  line `(ii) admit the document in evidence notwithstanding that it is not duly stamped, if such`
  line `document is otherwise admissible in evidence.]`
obj_root_law_sections_10_d:
  sectionId (2216)
  sectionNo 10D
  orderNo 14
  title `Power to stop and seize conveyances.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_10_d_content
  footnotes `1. Ins. by Act 40 of 1984, s. 5 (w.e.f. 2-7-1984).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_11_12_00004_196322_1517807320141&sectionId=2216&sectionno=10D&orderno=14&orgactid=AC_CEN_11_12_00004_196322_1517807320141
obj_root_law_sections_10_d_content:
  string
  line `^1[10D. Power to stop and seize conveyances.--Any authorised officer may, if he has any reason to`
  line `suspect that any conveyance or animal is being, or is about to be, used for the transportation of any`
  line `commodity which is liable to confiscation under this Act and that by such transportation any provision of`
  line `this Act has been, is being or is about to be, contravened at anytime, stop such conveyance or animal or,`
  line `in the case of an aircraft, compel it to land, and--`
  line
  line `(a) rummage and search the conveyance or any part thereof,`
  line
  line `(b) examine and search any goods or materials in the conveyance or on the animal,`
  line
  line `(c) if it becomes necessary to stop any conveyance or animal, he may use all lawful means for`
  line `stopping it and where such means fail, the conveyance or animal may be fired upon,`
  line
  line `and where he is satisfied that it is necessary so to do prevent the contravention of any provision of this`
  line `Act, he may seize such conveyance or animal.`
  line
  line `Explanation.--Any reference in this section to a conveyance shall, unless the context otherwise`
  line `requires, be construed as including a reference to an aircraft, vehicle or vessel.]`
obj_root_law_sections_10_e:
  sectionId (2217)
  sectionNo 10E
  orderNo 15
  title `Search and seizure to be made in accordance with the Code of Criminal Procedure, 1973.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_10_e_content
  footnotes `1. Ins. by Act 40 of 1984, s. 5 (w.e.f. 2-7-1984).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_11_12_00004_196322_1517807320141&sectionId=2217&sectionno=10E&orderno=15&orgactid=AC_CEN_11_12_00004_196322_1517807320141
obj_root_law_sections_10_e_content:
  string
  line `^1[10E. Search and seizure to be made in accordance with the Code of Criminal Procedure,`
  line `1973.--The provisions of the Code of Criminal Procedure, 1973 (2 of 1974), relating to searches and`
  line `seizures shall, so far as may be, apply to every search or seizure made under this Act.]`
obj_root_law_sections_10_f:
  sectionId (2218)
  sectionNo 10F
  orderNo 16
  title Confiscation.
  content obj_root_law_sections_10_f_content
  footnotes `1. Ins. by Act 40 of 1984, s. 5 (w.e.f. 2-7-1984).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_11_12_00004_196322_1517807320141&sectionId=2218&sectionno=10F&orderno=16&orgactid=AC_CEN_11_12_00004_196322_1517807320141
obj_root_law_sections_10_f_content:
  string
  line `^1[10F. Confiscation.--Any commodity in respect of which--`
  line
  line `(a) a certificate has been obtained from an agency referred to in sub-section (1) of section 7`
  line `fraudulently or by misrepresentation, or`
  line
  line `(b) any provision of this Act has been, is being, or is attempted to be, contravened, shall, together`
  line `with any package, covering or receptacle in which such commodity is found, be liable to confiscation`
  line `and, where such commodity is so mixed with any other goods or materials that it cannot be readily`
  line `separated, such other goods or materials shall also be liable to confiscation:`
  line
  line `Provided that where it is established to the satisfaction of the adjudicating authority that any`
  line `commodity, which is liable to confiscation under this Act, belongs to a person other than the person who`
  line `has, by any act or omission, rendered it liable to confiscation, and such act or omission was without the`
  line `knowledge or connivance of the person to whom it belongs, such commodity shall not be ordered to be`
  line `confiscated; but such other action as is authorised by this Act may be taken against the person who has,`
  line `by such act or omission, rendered such commodity liable to confiscation.]`
obj_root_law_sections_10_g:
  sectionId (2219)
  sectionNo 10G
  orderNo 17
  title `Confiscation of conveyance.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_10_g_content
  footnotes `1. Ins. by Act 40 of 1984, s. 5 (w.e.f. 2-7-1984).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_11_12_00004_196322_1517807320141&sectionId=2219&sectionno=10G&orderno=17&orgactid=AC_CEN_11_12_00004_196322_1517807320141
obj_root_law_sections_10_g_content:
  string
  line `^1[10G. Confiscation of conveyance.--Any conveyance or animal which has been, is being, or is`
  line `attempted to be, used for the transport of any commodity which is liable to confiscation under this Act,`
  line `shall be liable to confiscation unless the owner of the conveyance or animal proves that it was, is being, or`
  line `is about to be, so used without the knowledge or connivance of the owner himself, his agent, if any, and`
  line `the person in charge of the conveyance or animal and that each of them had taken all reasonable`
  line `precautions against such use:`
  line
  line `Provided that in the case of a conveyance or animal used for the transport of goods or passengers for`
  line `hire, the owner of the conveyance or animal shall be given an option to pay, in lieu of confiscation of the`
  line `conveyance or animal, a fine not exceeding the value of the commodity which has been, is being, or is`
  line `attempted to be, transported by such conveyance or animal.]`
obj_root_law_sections_10_h:
  sectionId (2220)
  sectionNo 10H
  orderNo 18
  title `Option to pay fine in lieu of confiscation.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_10_h_content
  footnotes `1. Ins. by Act 40 of 1984, s. 5 (w.e.f. 2-7-1984).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_11_12_00004_196322_1517807320141&sectionId=2220&sectionno=10H&orderno=18&orgactid=AC_CEN_11_12_00004_196322_1517807320141
obj_root_law_sections_10_h_content:
  string
  line `^1[10H. Option to pay fine in lieu of confiscation.--Whenever confiscation of any commodity is`
  line `authorised by this Act, the officer adjudging it shall, without prejudice to the provisions of the proviso to`
  line `section 10G, give to the owner of the commodity an option to pay in lieu of confiscation such fine not`
  line `exceeding the value of the commodity.]`
obj_root_law_sections_10_i:
  sectionId (5493)
  sectionNo 10I
  orderNo 19
  title `Liability to penalty.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_10_i_content
  footnotes `1. Ins. by Act 40 of 1984, s. 5 (w.e.f. 2-7-1984).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_11_12_00004_196322_1517807320141&sectionId=5493&sectionno=10I&orderno=19&orgactid=AC_CEN_11_12_00004_196322_1517807320141
obj_root_law_sections_10_i_content:
  string
  line `^1[10-I. Liability to penalty.--Any person,--`
  line
  line `(a) who, in relation to any commodity, does or omits to do any act which act or omission would`
  line `render such commodity liable to confiscation under this Act, or abets the doing or omission of such`
  line `an act; or`
  line
  line `(b) who acquires possession of or is in any way concerned in carrying, removing, depositing,`
  line `keeping, concealing, selling or purchasing, or in any manner dealing with, any commodity which he`
  line `knows or has reason to believe is liable to confiscation under this Act,`
  line
  line `shall be liable to a penalty not exceeding five times the value of the commodity or five thousand rupees,`
  line `whichever is more, whether or not such commodity has been confiscated or is available for confiscation.]`
obj_root_law_sections_10_j:
  sectionId (5494)
  sectionNo 10J
  orderNo 20
  title `Confiscation or penalty not to interfere with other punishments.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_10_j_content
  footnotes `1. Ins. by Act 40 of 1984, s. 5 (w.e.f. 2-7-1984).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_11_12_00004_196322_1517807320141&sectionId=5494&sectionno=10J&orderno=20&orgactid=AC_CEN_11_12_00004_196322_1517807320141
obj_root_law_sections_10_j_content:
  string
  line `^1[10J. Confiscation or penalty not to interfere with other punishments.--No confiscation made or`
  line `penalty imposed under the foregoing provisions of this Act shall prevent the infliction of any other`
  line `punishment to which the person affected thereby is liable under the provisions of this Act or under any`
  line `other law for the time being in force.]`
obj_root_law_sections_10_k:
  sectionId (5495)
  sectionNo 10K
  orderNo 21
  title Adjudication.
  content obj_root_law_sections_10_k_content
  footnotes `1. Ins. by Act 40 of 1984, s. 5 (w.e.f. 2-7-1984).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_11_12_00004_196322_1517807320141&sectionId=5495&sectionno=10K&orderno=21&orgactid=AC_CEN_11_12_00004_196322_1517807320141
obj_root_law_sections_10_k_content:
  string
  line `^1[10K. Adjudication.--Any confiscation may be adjudged or penalty may be imposed under this Act`
  line `by the Director of Inspection and Quality Control, or, where he so directs, by a general or special order,`
  line `by any officer subordinate to him.]`
obj_root_law_sections_10_l:
  sectionId (5496)
  sectionNo 10L
  orderNo 22
  title `Giving of opportunity to the owner of goods etc.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_10_l_content
  footnotes `1. Ins. by Act 40 of 1984, s. 5 (w.e.f. 2-7-1984).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_11_12_00004_196322_1517807320141&sectionId=5496&sectionno=10L&orderno=22&orgactid=AC_CEN_11_12_00004_196322_1517807320141
obj_root_law_sections_10_l_content:
  string
  line `^1b@[10L. Giving of opportunity to the owner of goods etc.--No order of adjudication of confiscation or`
  line `imposing a penalty shall be made unless the owner of the commodity, conveyance or animal or other`
  line `person concerned is given a notice in writing--`
  line
  line `(a) informing him of the grounds on which it is proposed to confiscate such commodity,`
  line `conveyance or animal or to impose a penalty;`
  line
  line `(b) giving him a reasonable opportunity of making a representation in writing within such`
  line `reasonable time as may be specified in the notice against the confiscation or imposition of penalty`
  line `mentioned therein, and, if he so desires, of being heard in the matter.]`
obj_root_law_sections_10_m:
  sectionId (5497)
  sectionNo 10M
  orderNo 23
  title Appeal
  content obj_root_law_sections_10_m_content
  footnotes `1. Ins. by Act 40 of 1984, s. 5 (w.e.f. 2-7-1984).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_11_12_00004_196322_1517807320141&sectionId=5497&sectionno=10M&orderno=23&orgactid=AC_CEN_11_12_00004_196322_1517807320141
obj_root_law_sections_10_m_content:
  string
  line `^1@[10M. Appeal.--(1) Any person aggrieved by any decision or order made under this Act may prefer`
  line `an appeal,--`
  line
  line `(a) where the decision or order has been made by the Director of Inspection and Quality Control,`
  line `to the Central Government;`
  line
  line `(b) where the decision or order has been made by any officer subordinate to the Director of`
  line `Inspection and Quality Control, to the Director of Inspection and Quality Control.`
  line
  line `within a period of forty-five days from the date on which the decision or order is served on such person:`
  line
  line `Provided that the appellate authority may if it is satisfied that the appellant was prevented by`
  line `sufficient cause from preferring the appeal within the aforesaid period of forty-five days, allow such`
  line `appeal to be preferred within a further period of forty-five days:`
  line
  line `Provided further that in the case of an appeal against an order imposing a penalty, no such appeal`
  line `shall be entertained unless the amount of the penalty has been deposited by the appellant:`
  line
  line `Provided also that where the appellate authority is of the opinion that the deposit to be made will`
  line `cause undue hardship to the appellant, it may at its discretion, dispense with such deposit either`
  line `unconditionally or subject to such conditions as it may impose.`
  line
  line `(2) The appellate authority may, after giving to the appellant a reasonable opportunity of being heard,`
  line `if he so desires, and after making such further inquiries, if any, as it may consider necessary, pass such`
  line `orders as it thinks fit, confirming modifying or reversing the decision or order appealed against or may`
  line `send back the case, with such directions as it may think fit, for afresh adjudication or decision, as the case`
  line `may be, after taking additional evidence, if necessary:`
  line
  line `Provided that an order enhancing or imposing a penalty or confiscating commodity of a greater value`
  line `shall not be made under this section unless the appellant has had an opportunity of making a`
  line `representation and, if he so desires, of being heard, in his defence.]`
obj_root_law_sections_10_n:
  sectionId (5498)
  sectionNo 10N
  orderNo 24
  title `Powers of revision.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_10_n_content
  footnotes `1. Ins. by Act 40 of 1984, s. 5 (w.e.f. 2-7-1984).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_11_12_00004_196322_1517807320141&sectionId=5498&sectionno=10N&orderno=24&orgactid=AC_CEN_11_12_00004_196322_1517807320141
obj_root_law_sections_10_n_content:
  string
  line `^1[10N. Powers of revision.--The Central Government may, on its own motion or otherwise, call for`
  line `and examine the records of any proceeding in which an order of adjudication of confiscation or imposing`
  line `any penalty has been made by any officer under this Act and against which no appeal has been preferred,`
  line `for the purpose of satisfying itself as to the correctness, legality or propriety of such order or decision and`
  line `pass such orders thereon as it may think fit:`
  line
  line `Provided that no decision or order shall be varied under this section so as to prejudicially affect any`
  line `person unless such person--`
  line
  line `(a) has, within a period of two years from the date of such decision or order, received a notice to`
  line `show cause why such decision or order shall not be varied, and`
  line
  line `(b) has been given a reasonable opportunity of making a representation and, if he so desires, of`
  line `being heard in his defence.]`
obj_root_law_sections_10_o:
  sectionId (5499)
  sectionNo 10O
  orderNo 25
  title `Powers of adjudicating and other authorities.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_10_o_content
  footnotes `1. Ins. by Act 40 of 1984, s. 5 (w.e.f. 2-7-1984).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_11_12_00004_196322_1517807320141&sectionId=5499&sectionno=10O&orderno=25&orgactid=AC_CEN_11_12_00004_196322_1517807320141
obj_root_law_sections_10_o_content:
  string
  line `^1[10-O. Powers of adjudicating and other authorities.--(1) Every authority making any adjudication`
  line `or hearing any appeal or exercising any powers of revision under this Act shall have all the powers of a`
  line `civil court under the Code of Civil Procedure, 1908 (5 of 1908), while trying a suit, in respect of the`
  line `following matters, namely:--`
  line
  line `(a) a summoning and enforcing the attendance of witnesses;`
  line
  line `(b) requiring the discovery and production of any document;`
  line
  line `(c) requisitioning any public record or copy thereof from any court or office;`
  line
  line `(d) receiving evidence on affidavits; and`
  line
  line `(e) issuing commissions for the examination of witnesses or documents.`
  line
  line `(2) Every authority making any adjudication or hearing any appeal or exercising any powers of`
  line `revision under this Act shall be deemed to be a Civil Court for the purposes of sections 345and 346 of the`
  line `Code of Criminal Procedure, 1973 (2 of 1974).`
  line
  line `(3) Every authority making any adjudication or hearing any appeal or exercising any powers of`
  line `revision under this Act shall have the power to make such orders of an interim nature as it may think fit`
  line `and may also, for sufficient cause, order the stay of operation of any decision or order.]`
obj_root_law_sections_10_p:
  sectionId (5500)
  sectionNo 10P
  orderNo 26
  title `Continuance of proceedings in the event of death or insolvency`
  content obj_root_law_sections_10_p_content
  footnotes `1. Ins. by Act 40 of 1984, s. 5 (w.e.f. 2-7-1984).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_11_12_00004_196322_1517807320141&sectionId=5500&sectionno=10P&orderno=26&orgactid=AC_CEN_11_12_00004_196322_1517807320141
obj_root_law_sections_10_p_content:
  string
  line `^1[10P. Continuance of proceedings in the event of death or insolvency.--(1) Where a penalty has`
  line `been imposed by the adjudicating authority and--`
  line
  line `(a) no appeal against the order imposing such penalty has been preferred to the Appellate`
  line `authority and the person entitled to file such appeal dies or is adjudicated an insolvent before the`
  line `expiry of the period within which the appeal can be preferred; or`
  line
  line `(b) an appeal has been preferred to the Appellate Authority against the order imposing such`
  line `penalty but the appellant dies or is adjudicated an insolvent during the pendency of the appeal,`
  line
  line `then, it shall be lawful for the legal representatives, of such person or the Official Assignee or the Official`
  line `Receiver, as the case may be, to prefer an appeal to the appellate authority or, as the case may be, to`
  line `continue the appeal before the Appellate authority, in place of such person and the provisions of section`
  line `10M shall, so far as may be, apply or continue to apply to such appeal.`
  line
  line `(2) The powers of the Official Assignee or the Official Receiver under sub-section (1) shall be`
  line `exercised by him subject to the provisions of the Presidency-towns Insolvency Act, 1909 (3 of 1909), or`
  line `the Provincial Insolvency Act, 1920 (5 of 1920), as the case may be.]`
obj_root_law_sections_11:
  sectionId (5501)
  sectionNo (11)
  orderNo 27
  title Penalty
  content obj_root_law_sections_11_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by Act 40 of 1984, s. 6, for "two year" (w.e.f. 2-7-1984).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_11_12_00004_196322_1517807320141&sectionId=5501&sectionno=11&orderno=27&orgactid=AC_CEN_11_12_00004_196322_1517807320141
obj_root_law_sections_11_content:
  string
  line `(1) If any person contravenes any order under clause (d) of section 6, or fraudulently`
  line `obtains a certificate under section 7, or fraudulently affixes or applies any such mark or seal as is referred`
  line `to in sub-section (1) of section 8, he shall, on conviction, be punishable--`
  line
  line `(i) for the first offence, with imprisonment for a term which may extend to two years, or with fine`
  line `which may extend to five thousand rupees, or with both;`
  line
  line `(ii) for the second or subsequent three offence, with imprisonment for a term which may extend`
  line `to ^1[three years] and also with fine which may extend to five thousand rupees and in the absence of`
  line `special and adequate reasons to be mentioned in the judgment of the court, such imprisonment shall`
  line `not be less than three months.`
  line
  line `(2)Any person who attempts to commit or abets the commission of an offence punishable under subsection`
  line `(1) shall be deemed to have committed such offence.`
  line
  line `(3) If any person contravenes or attempts to contravene or abets the contravention of any other`
  line `provision of this Act or any rules or orders made thereunder, he shall be punishable with fine which may`
  line `extend to one thousand rupees.`
obj_root_law_sections_11_a:
  sectionId (5502)
  sectionNo 11A
  orderNo 28
  title `Penalty for contravention of order made by adjudicating authority or Appellate authority.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_11_a_content
  footnotes `1. Ins. by s. 7, ibid. (w.e.f. 2-7-1984).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_11_12_00004_196322_1517807320141&sectionId=5502&sectionno=11A&orderno=28&orgactid=AC_CEN_11_12_00004_196322_1517807320141
obj_root_law_sections_11_a_content:
  string
  line `^1[11A. Penalty for contravention of order made by adjudicating authority or Appellate`
  line `authority.--If any person fails to pay the penalty imposed by the adjudicating or the Appellate authority`
  line `or fails to comply with any direction or order made, or deemed to have been made, under this Act, he`
  line `shall, on conviction, be punishable with imprisonment for a term which may extend to two years, or with`
  line `fine, or with both.]`
obj_root_law_sections_11_b:
  sectionId (5503)
  sectionNo 11B
  orderNo 29
  title `Offences by officers and employees of agency, etc.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_11_b_content
  footnotes `1. Ins. by s. 7, ibid. (w.e.f. 2-7-1984).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_11_12_00004_196322_1517807320141&sectionId=5503&sectionno=11B&orderno=29&orgactid=AC_CEN_11_12_00004_196322_1517807320141
obj_root_law_sections_11_b_content:
  string
  line `^1[11B. Offences by officers and employees of agency, etc.--(1) If any officer or employee of the`
  line `Council or of any agency referred to in sub-section (1) of section 7, or any surveyor, sampler or employee`
  line `of any testing house, referred to in sub-section (2) of that section enters into, or acquiesces in, any`
  line `agreement to do, abstains from doing, permits, conceals or connives at, any act or thing whereby any`
  line `provision of this Act is or may be contravened, he shall, on conviction, be punishable with imprisonment`
  line `for a term which may extend to two years, or with fine which may extend to five thousand rupees, or with`
  line both.
  line
  line `(2) If any officer searches or authorises any other officer of the Central Government to search any`
  line `place without having reason to believe that any commodity, books of account or documents or things of`
  line `the nature referred to in section 10Bare secreted in that place, he shall, on conviction, be punishable`
  line `withimprisonment for a term which may extend to six months, or with fine which may extend to one`
  line `thousand rupees, or with both.`
  line
  line `(3) If any officer or employee of the Council or of any agency referred to in sub-section (1) of section`
  line `7, or any surveyor, sampler or employee of any testing house, referred to sub-section (2) of that section,`
  line `except in the discharge in good faith of his duty as such officer or employee or in compliance with any`
  line `requisition made under any law for the time being in force, discloses any particulars learnt by him in his`
  line `official capacity in respect of any commodity, he shall, on conviction, be punishable with imprisonment`
  line `for a term which may extend to six months, or with fine which may extend to one thousand rupees, or`
  line `with both.]`
obj_root_law_sections_11_c:
  sectionId (5504)
  sectionNo 11C
  orderNo 30
  title `Correction of clerical or arithmetical mistakes.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_11_c_content
  footnotes `1. Ins. by s. 7, ibid. (w.e.f. 2-7-1984).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_11_12_00004_196322_1517807320141&sectionId=5504&sectionno=11C&orderno=30&orgactid=AC_CEN_11_12_00004_196322_1517807320141
obj_root_law_sections_11_c_content:
  string
  line `^1[11C. Correction of clerical or arithmetical mistakes.--Clerical or arithmetical mistakes in any`
  line `decision or order, or errors arising therein from any accidental slip or omission may, at any time, be`
  line `corrected by the authority by which the decision or order was made either on its own motion or on the`
  line `application of the aggrieved person:`
  line
  line `Provided that where any correction proposed to be made under this section will have the effect of`
  line `prejudicially affecting any person, no such correction shall be made except after giving to that person a`
  line `reasonable opportunity of making a representation in the matter and no such correction shall be made`
  line `after the expiry of a period of two years from the date on which such decision or order was made.]`
obj_root_law_sections_12:
  sectionId (5505)
  sectionNo (12)
  orderNo 31
  title `Offences by companies.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_12_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_12_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_11_12_00004_196322_1517807320141&sectionId=5505&sectionno=12&orderno=31&orgactid=AC_CEN_11_12_00004_196322_1517807320141
obj_root_law_sections_12_content:
  string
  line `(1) Where an offence under this Act has been committed by a`
  line `company, every person who, at the time the offence was committed, was in charge of, and was`
  line `responsible to, the company for the conduct of the business of the company, as well as the company, shall`
  line `be deemed to be guilty of the offence and shall be liable to be proceeded against and punished`
  line `accordingly:`
  line
  line `Provided that nothing contained in this sub-section shall render any such person liable to any`
  line `punishment, if he proves that the offence was committed without his knowledge or that he exercised all`
  line `due diligence to prevent the commission of such offence.`
  line
  line `(2) Notwithstanding anything contained in sub-section (1), where an offence under this Act has been`
  line `committed by a company and it is proved that the offence has been committed with the consent or`
  line `connivance of, or is attributable to any negligence on the part of, any director, manager, secretary or other`
  line `officer of the company, such director, manager, secretary or other officer shall also be deemed to be guilty`
  line `of that offence and shall be liable to be proceeded against and punished accordingly.`
  line
  line `Explanation.--For the purposes of this section,--`
  line
  line `(a) "company" means a body corporate and includes a firm or other association of individuals;`
  line and
  line
  line `(b) "director", in relation to a firm, means a partner in the firm.`
obj_root_law_sections_12_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_13:
  sectionId (5506)
  sectionNo (13)
  orderNo 32
  title `Delegation of powers.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_13_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_13_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_11_12_00004_196322_1517807320141&sectionId=5506&sectionno=13&orderno=32&orgactid=AC_CEN_11_12_00004_196322_1517807320141
obj_root_law_sections_13_content:
  string
  line `The Central Government may, by notification in the Official Gazette,`
  line `direct that any power exercisable by it under this Act shall, in relation to such matters and subject to such`
  line `conditions, if any, as may be specified in the direction, be exercisable also b--`
  line
  line `(a) the Council;`
  line
  line `(b) such officer or authority subordinate to the Central Government, or such State Government or`
  line `such officer or authority subordinate to a State Government as may be specified in the direction.`
obj_root_law_sections_13_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_14:
  sectionId (5507)
  sectionNo (14)
  orderNo 33
  title `Procedure for prosecution.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_14_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_14_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_11_12_00004_196322_1517807320141&sectionId=5507&sectionno=14&orderno=33&orgactid=AC_CEN_11_12_00004_196322_1517807320141
obj_root_law_sections_14_content:
  string
  line `No prosecution for an offence punishable under this Act shall be`
  line `instituted except by or with the consent of an officer authorised by the Central Government by general or`
  line `special order in this behalf.`
obj_root_law_sections_14_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_15:
  sectionId (5508)
  sectionNo (15)
  orderNo 34
  title `Officers and employees of agency to be public servants.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_15_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_15_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_11_12_00004_196322_1517807320141&sectionId=5508&sectionno=15&orderno=34&orgactid=AC_CEN_11_12_00004_196322_1517807320141
obj_root_law_sections_15_content:
  string
  line `All officers and employees of the`
  line `Council or of any agency established or recognised under sub-section (1) of section 7and all surveyors,`
  line `samplers and employees of testing houses, referred to in sub-section (2) of that section shall, while acting`
  line `or purporting to act in pursuance of the provisions of this Act or any rule or order made there under, be`
  line `deemed to be public servants within the meaning of section 21 of the Indian Penal Code (45 of 1860).`
obj_root_law_sections_15_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_16:
  sectionId (5509)
  sectionNo (16)
  orderNo 35
  title `Protection of action taken in good faith.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_16_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_16_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_11_12_00004_196322_1517807320141&sectionId=5509&sectionno=16&orderno=35&orgactid=AC_CEN_11_12_00004_196322_1517807320141
obj_root_law_sections_16_content:
  string
  line `(1) No suit, prosecution or other legal proceeding`
  line `shall lie against the Council or any officer or employee of the Government or the Council or any agency`
  line `referred to in sub-section (1) of section 7 for anything which is in good faith done or intended to be done`
  line `in pursuance of this Act or any rule or order made thereunder.`
  line
  line `(2) No suit or other legal proceeding shall lie against the Government for any damage caused or likely`
  line `to be caused by anything which is in good faith done or intended to be done in pursuance of this Act or`
  line `any rule or order made thereunder.`
obj_root_law_sections_16_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_16_a:
  sectionId (5510)
  sectionNo 16A
  orderNo 36
  title `Suspension, etc., of operation of the provisions of the Act.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_16_a_content
  footnotes `1. Ins. by Act 40 of 1984, s. 8 (w.e.f. 2-7-1984).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_11_12_00004_196322_1517807320141&sectionId=5510&sectionno=16A&orderno=36&orgactid=AC_CEN_11_12_00004_196322_1517807320141
obj_root_law_sections_16_a_content:
  string
  line `^1[16A. Suspension, etc., of operation of the provisions of the Act.--(1) If the Central Government`
  line `is satisfied that circumstances exist which render it necessary or expedient so to do in the public interest,`
  line `it may, by notification in the Official Gazette, suspend or relax to a specified extent, the operation of all or`
  line `any of the provisions of this Act in respect of such notified commodity or commodities generally or in`
  line `respect of any area and for such period as may be specified in the notification.`
  line
  line `(2) Where the operation of any provision of this Act has, under sub-section (1), been suspended or`
  line `relaxed, such suspension or relaxation may, at any time be removed by the Central Government by a like`
  line notification.
  line
  line `(3) Every notification issued under this section shall be laid, as soon as may be after it is issued,`
  line `before each House of Parliament, while it is in session, for a total period of thirty days which may be`
  line `comprised in one session or in two or more successive sessions, and if before the expiry of the session`
  line `immediately following the session or the successive sessions aforesaid, both Houses agree in making any`
  line `modification in the notification or both Houses agree that the notification should not be issued, the`
  line `notification shall thereafter have effect only in such modified form or be of no effect, as the case may be;`
  line `so, however, that any such modification or annulment shall be without prejudice to the validity of`
  line `anything previously done under that notification.]`
obj_root_law_sections_17:
  sectionId (5511)
  sectionNo (17)
  orderNo 37
  title `Power to make rules.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_17_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_17_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_11_12_00004_196322_1517807320141&sectionId=5511&sectionno=17&orderno=37&orgactid=AC_CEN_11_12_00004_196322_1517807320141
obj_root_law_sections_17_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Central Government may, by notification in the Official Gazette,`
  line `make rules to carry out the purposes of this Act.`
  line
  line `(2) In particular and without prejudice to the generality of the foregoing power, such rules may`
  line `provide for--`
  line
  line `(a) the travelling and daily allowances payable to members of the Council, persons co-opted`
  line `under sub-section (2) of section 5, and members of specialist committees referred to in sub-section (3)`
  line `of that section;`
  line
  line `(b) the functions of the Council and the procedure to be followed by it;`
  line
  line `(c) the appointment of officers and other employees of the Council;`
  line
  line `(d) the procedure to be followed for various types of quality control and inspection;`
  line
  line `(e) the conditions which a testing house, surveyor or sampler should satisfy for purposes of`
  line `approval by the Central Government;`
  line
  line `(f) the fees chargeable for purposes of examination and issue of certificates under section 7;`
  line
  line `^1[(ff) the manner in which, and the procedure subject to which, any certificate issued`
  line `under sub-section (3) of section 7 shall be amended, suspended or cancelled;]`
  line
  line `(g) the filing of appeals under section 7 and the fees payable therefore;`
  line
  line `^1[(gg) the authority or person by which or by whom, and the manner in which, any document`
  line `received from a place outside India shall be authenticated;]`
  line
  line `(h) the manner in which the accounts of the Council shall be maintained and audited;`
  line
  line `(i) any other matter which is required to be, or may be, prescribed.`
  line
  line `(3) Every rule made by the Central Government under this section shall be laid as soon as may be`
  line `after it is made before each House of Parliament while it is in session for a total period of thirty days`
  line `which may be comprised in one session or in two or more successive sessions, and if, before the expiry of`
  line `the session ^2[immediately following the session] or the successive sessions aforesaid, both Houses agree`
  line `in making any modification in the rule or both Houses agree that the rule should not be made, the rule`
  line `shall thereafter have effect only in such modified form or be of no effect, as the case may be; so however`
  line `that any such modification or annulment shall be without prejudice to the validity of anything previously`
  line `done under that rule.`
obj_root_law_sections_17_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Ins. by s. 9, ibid. (w.e.f. 2-7-1984).`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by Act 40 of 1984, s. 9, for "immediately following the session", (w.e.f. 2-7-1984).`
obj_root_law_sections_18:
  sectionId (5512)
  sectionNo (18)
  orderNo 38
  title `Act to over-ride other enactments.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_18_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_18_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_11_12_00004_196322_1517807320141&sectionId=5512&sectionno=18&orderno=38&orgactid=AC_CEN_11_12_00004_196322_1517807320141
obj_root_law_sections_18_content:
  string
  line `As from the date on which a commodity is notified under`
  line `clause (a) of section 6, the provisions of this Act or anything done or any action taken there under shall`
  line `have effect in relation to that commodity notwithstanding any provisions (relating to quality control and`
  line `inspection prior to the export of such commodity) contained in any enactment other than this Act or in`
  line `any instrument having effect by virtue of any enactment other than this Act.`
obj_root_law_sections_18_footnotes:
  string
  line
